# run.log — ATOM-106 (reinstall path, kit v0.3.2)

[breath] Mandate read (ATOM-106-LAUNCH.md canonical, INFO-040 verbatim spec).
CEO met a raw «fatal: destination path 'framework' already exists» after
uninstall+reclone. framework/ is recreatable by construction; everything
next to it is the founder's. Design question: WHERE does the gate live and
when must it stay silent.

[design] Gate placement: (1) resumed entry — after step_language (dialog in
the restored locale), only when the install is COMPLETE (STEP_MACHINEWIDE
done); a mid-interview resume passes through untouched — the idempotent
walkthrough IS its recovery (scenario 2 stays byte-green). (2) fresh entry —
inside step_workdir right after the folder answer, BEFORE pointer/state are
written, so «отмена»/«нет» leave without a trace. Fresh entry with a
foreign state in the chosen folder (re-cloned kit, pointer lost) ADOPTS the
state first — reinstall then walks the recorded answers with zero re-asks;
this run's q1 language wins over the stored one. The dialog functions sit
ABOVE step_language in the file, outside the question-inventory awk range —
same standing as the --apply-update confirmation (occupied-entry-only, not
part of the fresh interview).

[design] Purge tolerates every git half-state (dir present / dir gone with
index entry / .gitmodules section / .git/modules copy) — each one alone
kills `git submodule add` with exactly the CEO's fatal. Live data is
untouched by construction: purge names only framework/ and git plumbing.

[harness-catch — REAL BUG, first full run] Scenarios 3/5/10/12/15/17 all
red with one root cause: my purge deleted an EMPTIED .gitmodules from the
worktree. `git rm` on the last submodule leaves an EMPTY .gitmodules
registered in the index; a worktree-only deletion then kills the next
`git submodule add` with «please make sure that the .gitmodules file is in
the working tree». Reproduced in a minimal sandbox, fixed by leaving the
file to git, documented in the code. Re-run green.

